    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, this is a good start. Could you make it slightly more personal though? Mention that we really valued their specific expertise in CI/CD pipelines and that it was a very close call between them and the other candidate. I want them to feel like we really saw their talent, even if the Kubernetes piece was the deciding factor.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior DevOps Role\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to extend my sincerest gratitude for your interest in the Senior DevOps position at our Austin office and for the time you invested in the interview process. Your technical prowess, particularly in the realm of CI/CD pipelines, was truly impressive, and we were delighted to see your passion for DevOps.\n\nAfter careful consideration and a thorough review of all candidates, we have decided to move forward with another individual whose experience with Kubernetes orchestration aligns more closely with our current project requirements. This decision was not an easy one, as we were genuinely impressed with your skills and fit for our team. The expertise you brought to the table, especially in CI/CD pipelines, made this a very close call between you and another candidate.\n\nWe understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this decision was made with the best interest of our company and our projects in mind. We genuinely appreciate your patience and understanding throughout this process.\n\nWe encourage you to apply for future opportunities that may be a better fit for your skills and experience. We wish you the best of luck in your continued career journey and hope that you find",
